---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="i18n Example" noIndex={true}>
  <style slot="head">
    .container {
      margin-top: 64px;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 64px auto;
      padding: 48px;
    }
    code {
      background: var(--bg-soft);
      padding: 2px 8px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    pre {
      background: var(--bg-soft);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 16px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin: 16px 0;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <h1>i18n Example</h1>
    <p>This page demonstrates the i18n system used in World Stone Hub.</p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>
      Add <code>data-i18n="key.path"</code> to any element, and the text will be replaced with the translated
      string from <code>i18n.js</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>Examples</h2>
    <p data-i18n="nav.inicio">Este texto se reemplazará</p>
    <p data-i18n="nav.canteras">Este texto se reemplazará</p>

    <h2>Technical notes</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>i18n.js</code> script handles language switching via buttons with <code
        >data-lang</code
      > attribute.
    </p>
    <p>Translations are stored as a nested object in JavaScript.</p>
  </div>
</Page>
